  {'subject': 'Mathematics', 'year': 2014, 'question': "From a point, the angle of elevation of a plane is 60°. If the plane is 1000m high, find the horizontal distance (tan60=√3).", 'options': ['1000/√3 m', '1000√3 m', '500 m', '2000 m'], 'correctIndex': 0, 'explanation': "tan60 = height/distance → √3 = 1000/d → d = 1000/√3."},
  {'subject': 'Mathematics', 'year': 2015, 'question': "In a triangle, if angle of elevation from point A to top of building is 30°, and from point B (20m closer) it is 45°, find height (tan30=1/√3, tan45=1).", 'options': ['27.32 m', '20 m', '10 m', '40 m'], 'correctIndex': 0, 'explanation': "Let height h, distance from B = x, from A = x+20. tan45 = h/x → x=h. tan30 = h/(h+20) → 1/√3 = h/(h+20) → h+20 = h√3 → h(√3-1)=20 → h=20/(√3-1) ≈ 27.32."},
  {'subject': 'Mathematics', 'year': 2016, 'question': "Find the angle whose sine is 0.866 (3 decimal places) – use sin 60° = 0.866.", 'options': ['60°', '30°', '45°', '90°'], 'correctIndex': 0, 'explanation': "sin 60° ≈ 0.866."},
