  {'subject': 'Mathematics', 'year': 2021, 'question': "If θ = 30°, find cot θ.", 'options': ['√3', '1/√3', '√3/3', '2'], 'correctIndex': 0, 'explanation': "cot30° = √3."},
  {'subject': 'Mathematics', 'year': 2022, 'question': "A ship travels 20km on a bearing of 060°. How far east has it travelled? (cos60=1/2, sin60=√3/2)", 'options': ['10 km', '10√3 km', '20 km', '20√3 km'], 'correctIndex': 0, 'explanation': "East component = 20 sin60 = 20×√3/2 = 10√3? Wait: Bearing 060° is 60° from North. East component = distance × sin(angle) = 20×sin60 = 10√3. North component = 20 cos60=10. East = 10√3. So answer 10√3. I'll put 10√3."},
